SYSTEM DESIGN SUMMARY

PART 1 — Backend & Distributed Systems

Design URL Shortener
Tests unique ID generation, high read scalability, key-value storage, and redirect latency optimization.

Design Twitter / X
Tests massive social graph handling, feed generation models, high read/write scalability, and hot user mitigation.

Design Uber
Tests real-time geo-location streaming, nearest-neighbor matching, and high-concurrency state synchronization.

Design WhatsApp / Messenger
Tests low-latency message delivery, online/offline handling, persistence, and multi-device synchronization.

Design News Feed
Tests feed generation strategies, push vs pull tradeoffs, and caching hot content.

Design YouTube / Video Platform
Tests large file storage, video processing pipelines, CDN distribution, and streaming latency control.

Design Rate Limiter
Tests distributed counters, rate limiting algorithms, and precision vs performance tradeoffs.

Design Distributed Cache
Tests hot data caching, eviction policies, cache consistency, and sharding strategies.

Design API Gateway
Tests unified routing, authentication, rate limiting, monitoring, and service aggregation.

Design Notification System
Tests asynchronous processing, reliable delivery, retries, deduplication, and multi-channel messaging.

PART 2 — Infrastructure / Platform Systems

Design Logging System
Tests high-throughput ingestion, distributed storage, indexing, and efficient search.

Design Metrics / Telemetry Platform
Tests time-series ingestion, aggregation pipelines, compression, and fast queries.

Design File Storage System
Tests file chunking, replication, redundancy, metadata management, and high availability.

Design Search Engine
Tests inverted index construction, fast retrieval, ranking systems, and incremental indexing.

Design Job Scheduler
Tests task scheduling, dependency graphs, retry mechanisms, and distributed coordination.

Design Message Queue
Tests message durability, ordering guarantees, consumer scaling, and backpressure handling.

Design Feature Flag System
Tests real-time configuration rollout, consistency across services, and staged deployments.

Design Payment System
Tests strong consistency, idempotency, transaction integrity, reconciliation, and reliability.

PART 3 — Data / Realtime / Streaming Systems

Design Chat System
Tests real-time messaging protocols, session state management, and persistent storage.

Design Live Streaming Platform
Tests high-bandwidth video pipelines, ultra-low latency delivery, and massive audience scaling.

Design Stock Trading Platform
Tests ultra-low latency processing, strong consistency, order matching, and fault tolerance.

Design Real-Time Bidding System
Tests millisecond decision systems, high-throughput auctions, and real-time analytics.

Design Distributed Lock Service
Tests distributed mutual exclusion, fault recovery, lease expiration, and consensus mechanisms.

PART 4 — Core Engineering Concepts

Scalability
Horizontal scaling, load balancing, partitioning, sharding, hotspot mitigation.

High Availability & Reliability
Replication, failover, redundancy, fault tolerance, disaster recovery.

Consistency & Distributed Tradeoffs
CAP theorem, strong vs eventual consistency, quorum systems, distributed transactions.

Performance Engineering
Latency reduction, throughput optimization, caching, asynchronous processing.

Storage & Data Modeling
SQL vs NoSQL tradeoffs, indexing strategies, schema design, partition keys.

Messaging & Async Systems
Message queues, event-driven architectures, delivery guarantees, backpressure.

Caching Strategies
Cache-aside, write-through, write-back, invalidation strategies, CDN usage.

Traffic Management
Rate limiting, throttling, circuit breakers, API gateways.

Distributed Coordination
Leader election, heartbeats, consensus basics, distributed locks.

Observability & Operations
Logging, metrics, tracing, monitoring, alerting.

PART 5 — What Interviewers Evaluate

Structured problem solving
Clear architecture design
Understanding of tradeoffs
Scalability thinking
Engineering practicality
